And so to the extent that\npeople are not employable,
that there are barriers that are\npreventing them from achieving
wages and the human capital\ndevelopment that is necessary,
then our benchmark for\nwhat full employment
looks like or\nmaximized employment
is lower than it should be.
And so it's very important\nto me and to our institution
that we reach out\nand engage and try
to identify the\nbarriers to maximize
the number of employable\npeople in the workplace.
And we don't always have\nthe tools at the Fed,
but we do have a podium to stand\non and yell from and with that,
