is limited and constrained\npretty significantly.
And so segregation\nand discrimination,
the things that the Fair Housing\nAct really tried to attack,
were constraints to prevent\nAfrican-Americans and people
of other protected classes to be\nable to have housing in places
where the foundational elements,\nthe schools and the like,
would give them true\naccess to opportunity.
So there's a large literature\non the history of discrimination
in this country.
If you saw the New York Times\narticle or the editorial that
