So there were lots of\nAIs that came to HUD,
and HUD would take six,\neight years to review them.
And at that point, they\nwere kind of moot, right?
And so the GAO did an\nanalysis of this process.
And in the analysis,\nthey took a survey of AIs
that were on the shelves at HUD.
40% of them were\nolder than five years.
Now, the reg said\nyou're supposed
to do them every five years.
So 40% of them were\nolder than that.
11% were older than 10 years.
And it gives you a sense of\nhow HUD was engaging in this.
And once communities understood\nthat, they were clearly going
to do as little as necessary.
Just get a report\nup there, and then
do whatever you want to do.
So there really\nwasn't a commitment
to fair housing in\nan affirmative way.
So we come to 2008.
There's an election.
President Obama is\nelected, and Shaun Donovan
gets named and confirmed\nas the Secretary
